      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 1907: `loadMissingBodyOverwrites` stores shared `SwarmMessage` pointers under the history mutex, then dereferences and copies them after releasing the mutex while other paths can mutate `body`, `editions`, or `pluginData`. That creates a data race and can produce inconsistent plugin input. Store message IDs during collection, then re-lock to take a value snapshot before transforming and re-lock again to write the result.",
      "revId": "bad686d9b41474309af9e66cfb987a0e0b56435e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
