      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 151: The new plugin services, especially `editMessage`, `updateMessageBodyOverwrite`, and the global clear/reload services, trust caller-provided account and conversation IDs without checking that the calling plugin is enabled for that conversation. A loaded plugin can therefore edit messages or alter UI-visible message bodies across all accounts/conversations. Bind these services to the `DLPlugin*` caller and reject operations unless that plugin\u0027s chat handler is attached/allowed for the target conversation. Suggested pattern:\n```suggestion\n        if (!isPluginAllowedForConversation(plugin, cm-\u003eaccountId, cm-\u003epeerId))\n            return -1;\n```",
